Description of female. Body (
Fig. 12
) compact, holotype 1.4 mm long, about six times as long as wide. Cephalothorax subrectangular, with slight blunt rostrum, naked, eyes absent but rounded eyelobes present. Six free pereonites; pereonites 1 to 3 subequal, shorter than posterior pereonites, 0.3 times as long as cephalothorax; pereonites 4 and 5 subequal in length, just over twice as long as pereonite 1 ; pereonite 6 shorter, 0.7 times as long as pereonite 5 . Five free subequal pleonites bearing pleopods; each pleonite one-third as long as pereonite 6 . Pleotelson subrectangular, three times as long as last pleonite, with rounded extension mid-posteriorly.
